HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 103
BY REPRESENTATIVE CREWS
BUILDING CODES: Provides relative to backflow prevention inspection frequency
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana State Uniform Construction Code Council and the
3 Louisiana Department of Health to study and consider amending the provisions of
4 the amended International Plumbing Code, adopted as part of the Louisiana State
5 Uniform Construction Code, and the provisions of the Sanitary Code, regarding the
6 frequency of inspections and testing of backflow prevention devices, barometric
7 loops, and air gaps, and to promulgate any necessary rules or amendments to
8 implement a less frequent inspection and testing schedule.
9 WHEREAS, while backflow prevention is essential to protecting the public potable
10 water supply from contamination, the required annual frequency of inspections may exceed
11 what is reasonably necessary to ensure continued operability and safety in many residential
12 and low-hazard applications, thereby creating unnecessary financial burdens without
13 commensurate public health benefits; and
14 WHEREAS, these mandatory annual inspection and testing requirements impose
15 significant and recurring costs on homeowners, property owners, tenants, and other
16 responsible parties for the hiring of certified testers, documentation and record-keeping,
17 reporting to building officials or water suppliers, and any necessary repairs or replacements;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, modern backflow prevention assemblies manufactured to current
20 standards of the American Society of Sanitary Engineers and the American Water Works
21 Association are engineered with durable materials and reliable check valve mechanisms that
